<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">

    <intro>
        <p>Consider the function <m>f(x,y)= {{f}}</m>.</p>
    </intro>
    
    
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
                Compute the gradient vector <m>\nabla f(x,y)</m>.
        
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p>
                <m>\nabla f(x,y) = \bigl\langle {{fx}}, {{fy}} \bigr\rangle</m>.
            </p>
            </outtro>
        </knowl>
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
                Compute <m>\nabla f({{x0}},{{y0}})</m> and sketch this vector, with its initial point at <m>P({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>, on the contour plot of <m>f</m> shown below.
        
            </p>
            <p align='center'><image
            source="assets/PD3/generated/{{__seed__}}/contour.png"
            description="Contour plot of f(x,y)."/></p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p>
                The gradient at the indicated point is <m>\nabla f( {{x0}},{{y0}} ) = \bigl\langle {{fx0}},{{fy0}} \bigr\rangle.</m>
            </p>
            </outtro>
        </knowl>
        <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
                Directly compute the <m>D_{ \langle {{compute_dirx}},{{compute_diry}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>.
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p><m>D_{ \langle {{compute_dirx}},{{compute_diry}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}}) = {{compute_dir_ans}}</m></p>
        </outtro>
        </knowl>
        <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
                Use geometry to rank the values of the following directional derivatives from least to greatest (i.e. left to right on the number line). Justify your answer by sketching how the gradient and the direction vector are oriented with respect to each other.
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>D_{ \langle {{a0}},{{b0}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>, <m>\quad D_{ \langle {{a1}},{{b1}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>, <m>\quad D_{ \langle {{a2}},{{b2}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>, and <m>\quad D_{ \langle {{a3}},{{b3}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p>
                You answer should have four sketches and use whether the angle between the gradient and the direction vector is
                is acute, obtuse, or perpedicular to determine the order. To check your work, here are the values from least to greatest.
            </p>
            <p><m>D_{ \langle {{u0}},{{v0}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}}) = {{dw}}</m></p>
            <p><m>D_{ \langle {{u1}},{{v1}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}}) = {{dx}}</m></p>
            <p><m>D_{ \langle {{u2}},{{v2}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}}) = {{dy}}</m></p>
            <p><m>D_{ \langle {{u3}},{{v3}} \rangle }f({{x0}},{{y0}}) = {{dz}}</m>.</p>
            
            </outtro>
        </knowl>
    
</knowl>